results.deck: Obsidian is a California-based developer most famous for their PC RPGs.
results.description:
Founded by Chris Avellone, Chris Jones, Chris Parker, Darren Monahan, and Feargus Urquhart in 2003 after the collapse of Black Isle Studios, Obsidian Entertainment is most famous for developing PC role playing games.

Obsidian Entertainment started by taking over the development of sequels from Bioware. They first started with Knights of the Old Republic II - The Sith Lords and Neverwinter Nights 2. Both games had a heavy focus on dialogue and inter-party influence.

In their first original IP, Obsidian Entertainment released the spy-themed shooter-RPG Alpha Protocol on June 1, 2010.

On April 20 2009, Bethesda Softworks announced that a new game in the Fallout series, Fallout: New Vegas would be developed by Obsidian. Fallout: New Vegas was released on October 19, 2010.

On September 14, 2012, Obsidian Entertainment has announced a Project Eternity on crowd funding platform Kickstarter, on a pledge to drive 1.1 million US dollars for its development.

List of Games by Obsidian Entertainment

  • Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II - The Sith Lords (2004)
  • Neverwinter Nights 2 (2006)
  • Neverwinter Nights 2: Mask of the Betrayer (2007)
  • Neverwinter Nights 2: Storm of Zehir (2008)
  • Alpha Protocol (2010)
  • Fallout: New Vegas (2010)
  • Dungeon Siege III (2011)
  • South Park: The Stick of Truth (2013)
  • Project Eternity (2014)
  • Wheel of Time (In development, TBA)
